This paper deals with image classification and retrieval, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to handle the noise in user-supplied tags, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the statistics of the Flickr 100 Million Image dataset, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of calibration procedures to better predict objective annotations, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL).
